Gangsters raided a residential plot in Mai Mahiu, Naivasha, and slashed to death a son of a local trader and attacked several other tenants on Wednesday night.  One woman was raped during the 2 am attack. Five tenants, including three women, were left for dead after they were attacked using machetes.  The 10-member gang raided the house of 40-year-old Stephen Kariuki near Mai Mahiu town and seriously injured him.  Joseph Njoroge, a witness, said the gangsters turned their fury on neighbours who responded to Kariuki's distress call.  He said two men and three women who were seriously injured were rushed to Naivasha sub-County Hospital.  Mystery: Woman's body found in water tank  Accident victim crashed by another car moments after rescue   State to spend Sh13 billion on Mai Mahiu road redesign  Two die in Naivasha road accident Area police commander Samuel Waweru confirmed the incident, adding that they were holding one suspect.    Take a quick survey and help us improve our website!  Mtu mmoja achomwa kiasi cha kutotambulika na kufariki kwenye ajali Mai Mahiu  Mai Mahiu tanker crash leaves one person dead  Maasai herders paralyze transport along Mai Mahiu- Narok road over killing of cattle by speeding bus By Anthony Gitonga | 54 minutes ago By Reuters | 3 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 12 hours ago By Daniel Chege | 23 hours ago Who failed Uhuru Kenyatta?